however, burst damage, which was largely intended on being a form of damage mitigation, is now <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>equally</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> important.  currently it and healing is entirely unimportant as spells like slow mitigate nearly all damage.<br>
im not making any role less valuable, im making all roles more valuable, since environments are now more difficult. thats a good thing<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
I would greatly disagree with you about that. While wizards may not be the greatest in groups they are among the strongest raiding classes (espcially in PoP) where their ability to turn out burst damage is a huge assest. To ofset their weakness in groups they are among the finest of soloing classes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
i dont think you should compair soloing to grouping, or raiding to grouping, those are different environments. <br>
one class should not be bad in grouping and make it up <br>
in soloing, or good at raiding and bad at soloing, ect ect. all classes should be reasonably effective in both raiding and grouping.<br>
<br>
i agree with verant, in that soloing should be an obviously inferior choice to grouping for all classes. all classes should want to group over solo as its more in line with the game. all classes should be bad at soloing. soloing, if done by our definition &quot;well&quot;, is better exp than groups, which are harder to set up. thats unbalanced.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
I understand that your trying to increase your (and other damage dealing casters) to groups but in the end I feel your suggestions would only make matters worse. Looks to me like your just trying to juggle around the classes which make up the &quot;holy trinity&quot; and not really solving the problem.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
im trying to put all classes in the holy trinity. all classes should perform a required role. all classes do, except the damage dealing classes.<br>
<br>
i disagree that this would make anything worse hower. making classes more dependant on each other is really a good thing, as it make the game more rewarding to play since it is more challenging, and more players feel included (as opposed to currently, the lone wizard necro or mage who feels left out since they do not perform a vital role). <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Too be honest, I am having less of an issue finding xp groups now in PoP then ever before and I am one of those rare Necromancers that hates soloing. PoP, once again, redefined the Necromancer class and this time I actually like the new role.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
im not a necromancer, but what new role to necromancers have? i always assumed the necromancer was good sustained damage with nice utility, and decent ability to mitigate damage. has this changed? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A> at: 11/21/02 10:19:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc@themagicianstower>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1288<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 11:13:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=410.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: dps</span><hr size=1> wow that is the longest post I have ever seen. EEKKK!!<br>
<br>
Anyway I have to say I totally disagree with your ideas. I think things are just fine right now. I think you are down playing the power of burst dps. I have said many times that in a experience group with a wizard kills are faster then with a rogue. With all the new mana regen spells that classes have, in a group setting a wizard easily replaces a rogue, same goes for mages. Soloing isn't hated by Verant, and they have never said that. Please post the link to back up that statement. Verant hated the fact that people could gain experience better soloing then grouping so they put in things to change that and it has hurt some soloing classes.<br>
<br>
However the experience reward in PoP is so great that it offsets really the ability to solo. There is much more to do in EQ then experience and when not able to get a group people should quest or work on trade skills. Those features are in the game for a reason. I solo just fine in UP right now and once i get more aa I will be back to gaining experience like I did before. I think the solo issue is a concern but being overplayed. <br>
<br>
All classes play a role in grouping, and burst dps is even more important do to mobs low hps. I don't have much of a problem getting a group so I really don't understand why the need to nerf slow ect...I happen to like soloing and it kills the time when I just don't want to group. I solo just fine in UP with just the level 61 spells. Grab a kei, buff up the 61 air pet and go to work. People need to be more inventive.  Also you have to understand that PoP isnt the only place to gain experience now. With the increased levels places like HoT become farming territory for a 6 man group. Same with jugs in sebillis and shrooms. The caves in UP are hella experience even now and are trivial do to the new burst dps of casters. Please look at the entire picture. There is more to EQ then PoP.<br>
